<topic topic-id="DFanZonestab" xmlns:fn="http://www.w3.org/2005/02/xpath-functions">
  <title>Fan Zones tab</title>
  <source>/120814-042457/Help/en/topics/DFanZonestab.xml</source>
  <keywords>fan zones zone fan</keywords>
  <intro />
  <sections>
    <section>
      <desc />
      <content>
        <p class="tablespacerbefore" />
        <table width="100%" style="border-collapse:collapse;" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="2">
          <tr>
            <th class="tableheading" style="border:1px solid #010101;text-align:left;">Column
</th>
            <th class="tableheading" style="border:1px solid #010101;text-align:left;">Description
</th>
          </tr>
          <tr valign="top">
            <td style="border:1px solid #010101;" align="left">
              <p class="tablebodytext">Thermal Zone
</p>
            </td>
            <td style="border:1px solid #010101;" align="left">
              <p class="tablebodytext">The four cooling zones in the enclosure: top left, top right, bottom left and bottom right
</p>
            </td>
          </tr>
          <tr valign="top">
            <td style="border:1px solid #010101;" align="left">
              <p class="tablebodytext">Zone Speed
</p>
            </td>
            <td style="border:1px solid #010101;" align="left">
              <p class="tablebodytext">The computed fan speed required based on the highest device need in the zone.
</p>
            </td>
          </tr>
          <tr valign="top">
            <td style="border:1px solid #010101;" align="left">
              <p class="tablebodytext">Device Bays
</p>
            </td>
            <td style="border:1px solid #010101;" align="left">
              <p class="tablebodytext">The number of the device bays in a particular thermal zone.
</p>
            </td>
          </tr>
          <tr valign="top">
            <td style="border:1px solid #010101;" align="left">
              <p class="tablebodytext">Fan Bay
</p>
            </td>
            <td style="border:1px solid #010101;" align="left">
              <p class="tablebodytext">The fan bay number. Fans in bays 3 and 8 are shared between thermal zones.
</p>
            </td>
          </tr>
          <tr valign="top">
            <td style="border:1px solid #010101;" align="left">
              <p class="tablebodytext">Fan Status
</p>
            </td>
            <td style="border:1px solid #010101;" align="left">
              <p class="tablebodytext">The overall status of each fan. Possible values are Unknown, OK, Degraded, Failed, and Absent.
</p>
            </td>
          </tr>
          <tr valign="top">
            <td style="border:1px solid #010101;" align="left">
              <p class="tablebodytext">Fan Speed
</p>
            </td>
            <td style="border:1px solid #010101;" align="left">
              <p class="tablebodytext">The fan speed is displayed as a percentage of maximum RPM.
</p>
            </td>
          </tr>
        </table>
        <p class="bodytext">The Zone Speed (targeted zone speed) and the Fan Speed displayed in the table can be different when the fans are trying to match the targeted zone speed. Fan speeds are displayed in percentage of total capacity. Fans operating in a zone without any blades run at a minimum RPM of 30% to maintain proper cooling for the entire enclosure. Click the Fan Zones tab to refresh the fan zone information displayed.</p>
        <p class="bodytext">The front and rear graphical views below the table display the targeted zone speed for each fan zone.</p>
      </content>
    </section>
  </sections>
</topic>